    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This collection of nearly 300 pictorial postcards of the Brooklyn Bridge features both black and white and color images of the bridge dating from about 1900 to 1984. The collection features views from both sides of the East River, of the bridge and the changing cityscapes of both Manhattan and Brooklyn, during the course of nearly 100 years. There are views from the air, from underneath the bridge, and also considerable sections of the city. The collection includes variant printings, colorings and additions. Some of the cards verge on the surreal, including a 1908 postcard depicting a car flying over the bridge. The collection contains both used cards with inscriptions and postal addresses as well as blank, unused cards.</field>
